<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A Maryland marriage license is valid for six months from the date it's issued. Your ceremony must happen within that window.</p>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">After the ceremony, your officiant signs the license. You've got 60 days to file the signed license back with the issuing Circuit Court. Don't skip this step. A signed license that doesn't get filed means the marriage isn't officially on record.</p>
