  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">"Can I see a full gallery from a single wedding, not just your highlight reel?"</strong> Highlight reels show a photographer's best 30 photos from dozens of weddings. A full gallery from one wedding shows you what the average shot looks like, how they handle low light, and whether the ceremony and reception images are as strong as the portrait session.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">"Have you shot at my venue before, and if not, will you do a venue walkthrough?"</strong> Photographers who've shot at Clipper Mill or Evergreen Museum know exactly where the light hits. New venues without a walkthrough produce more variable results.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">"What's your turnaround time for the full gallery?"</strong> Baltimore wedding photographers typically deliver galleries in 6 to 14 weeks. Anything over 14 weeks should come with a clear explanation.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">"What happens if you're sick or have an emergency on my wedding day?"</strong> Established photographers have backup arrangements. New photographers often don't. You need a direct answer to this question.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">"What's included in your packages: hours, number of photos, albums, second shooter?"</strong> Two photographers quoting $2,500 can have completely different deliverables. One might include a second shooter and album. The other might not.</li>
</ol>

<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight">How Do You Choose Between Similar Baltimore Photographers?</h2>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">When two photographers have similar portfolios and similar prices, here's what I'd look at. These are the things that actually determine whether you'll be happy with the experience, not just the photos.</p>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong class="text-charcoal">Communication speed.</strong> If a photographer takes four days to respond to your initial inquiry, that's what working with them will feel like for the next 12 to 18 months. Fast, warm responses early on are a reliable signal of how organized and professional the working relationship will be.</p>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong class="text-charcoal">Personality fit.</strong> You'll spend more time with your photographer than almost any other vendor on your wedding day. If the consultation call feels stiff or transactional, the photos often reflect that energy. The best wedding portraits happen when the couple's comfortable.</p>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-8"><strong class="text-charcoal">Consistency across venue types.</strong> Look at gallery images from indoor evening venues and outdoor afternoon ceremonies. Some photographers thrive in one setting and struggle in another. If your wedding is in Baltimore's interior spaces, make sure the photographer's indoor work is as strong as their outdoor portfolio.</p>

