<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight">What Does a Wedding Officiant Do in Maryland?</h2>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A Maryland wedding officiant performs the legal ceremony that makes your marriage valid. They must be legally recognized by the state, lead the ceremony from opening words through the vows and pronouncement, sign the marriage license immediately after the ceremony, and ensure the license gets filed with the issuing Circuit Court within 60 days.</p>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-8">Beyond the legal requirements, the officiant sets the entire emotional tone of your ceremony. They're the only vendor who's actively speaking for the full ceremony duration, and there's no way to edit it afterward. A good officiant makes the 20 to 30 minutes feel personal and meaningful. A stiff or disengaged one makes it feel transactional, regardless of how beautiful your venue is or how much you've spent on flowers.</p>

