<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900 mt-10 mb-4 tracking-tight">How Do You Choose the Right Maryland Wedding Venue?</h2>
<p class="text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The venue decision is where most Maryland wedding budgets succeed or fail. Here are the five questions that matter most before you sign a contract.</p>

<ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-4 text-charcoal-muted mb-8">
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">What's the catering policy?</strong> All-inclusive venues (in-house catering only) can add $50 to $100 per person in mandatory minimums. Open catering venues let you hire your own caterer and potentially save $2,000 to $6,000. Always ask before touring.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">What's not included in the venue fee?</strong> Tables, chairs, linens, sound system, lighting, parking attendants, and cleanup fees often aren't included. A $3,000 venue fee can become $5,000 after mandatory add-ons.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">What's the weather contingency?</strong> For outdoor Maryland venues, ask whether there's an indoor backup if it rains. If not, you're renting a tent ($1,500 to $4,000) as insurance.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">What are the noise and time restrictions?</strong> Many Maryland venues, especially in residential areas and parks, require music off by 10pm or 11pm. If you're planning a late reception, confirm the cutoff.</li>
  <li><strong class="text-charcoal">How far out are dates available?</strong> Popular Maryland venues book 12 to 18 months in advance for peak season Saturdays. If your preferred date is less than 6 months away, expect limited availability in Baltimore and Annapolis.</li>
</ol>

<div class="bg-cream border border-rose-light/40 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
  <p class="font-display font-semibold text-charcoal mb-2">Working with a Maryland wedding planner helps here.</p>
  <p class="text-sm text-charcoal-muted font-body mb-4">John has relationships with venues across the state and knows which ones have hidden costs, which ones are genuinely easy to work with, and which ones are worth the premium. He can narrow your venue search to the right two or three options for your budget and guest count.</p>
