<h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-charcoal mt-10 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions About Eloping in Maryland</h2>

<details class="bg-white border border-rose-light/40 rounded-lg mb-3" open>
  <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer">
    <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-charcoal">Can you elope in Maryland the same day you get the license?</h3>
  </summary>
  <div class="px-5 pb-5">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed">Yes. Most Maryland counties (including Baltimore City, Anne Arundel, Howard, Frederick, and Harford) issue marriage licenses immediately after you apply. There's no mandatory waiting period. You can apply in the morning and elope in the afternoon. Montgomery and Prince George's counties have historically required a 48-hour wait, so apply there two days before the ceremony. <a href="/blog/maryland-marriage-license" class="text-rose hover:underline">See the full county-by-county guide</a>.</p>
  </div>
