<details class="bg-white border border-rose-light/40 rounded-lg mb-3">
  <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer">
    <h3 class="font-display text-base font-semibold text-charcoal">Do you need witnesses to elope in Maryland?</h3>
  </summary>
  <div class="px-5 pb-5">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed">Yes. Maryland law requires one witness to be present at the ceremony and sign the marriage license. Most elopements have the photographer or planner serve as the witness, or one guest if you're bringing a small group. The witness signs the license at the ceremony alongside the officiant.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="bg-white border border-rose-light/40 rounded-lg mb-3">
  <summary class="flex items-center justify-between p-5 cursor-pointer">
