  </summary>
  <div class="px-5 pb-5">
    <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 font-light leading-relaxed">No. Eloping without family present or without informing family is completely legal. The legal requirements are just the marriage license, a registered officiant, and one witness. What you tell your family and when is entirely your decision. Many couples elope first and hold a celebration party for family later.</p>
  </div>
</details>

<details class="bg-white border border-rose-light/40 rounded-lg mb-8">
